After signing a global deal with Warner Music SA, Zandie Khumalo has now released her first single with the major label. A post shared by zandie Khumalo (@zandie_khumalo_gumede) on Nov 16, 2017 at 4:12pm PST The track, titled Nangu Makoti, is described as an old-school love song “slowly revealing itself as a next generation tribute to the union between man and woman.” And we on radio 💃🏽💃🏽💃🏽💃🏽💃🏽💃🏽💃🏽 #NanguMakoti @warnermusicsa A post shared by zandie Khumalo (@zandie_khumalo_gumede) on Nov 17, 2017 at 12:20am PST About her single, Zandie said in a statement: “I’m an advocate of love, my music has always been about encouraging people not to give up on love without turning a blind eye to the fact that it has its ups and downs. "With this single I took it up a notch, it’s about people who have gone through all the ups and down and came out stronger so we are now celebrating their love and the union of two families – it’s beautiful.” Listen to the full track here. 